00:42:35.200 --> 00:42:37.700
AUDIENCE: Yes, have there
been any specific interesting

00:42:37.700 --> 00:42:39.973
insights about the
X or Y chromosomes

00:42:39.973 --> 00:42:42.790
of Neanderthals
compared to ours?

00:42:49.070 --> 00:42:52.350
SVANTE PAABO: Very curiously,
these are female individuals

00:42:52.350 --> 00:42:57.640
so far, we have happened to
hit in those three individuals.

00:42:57.640 --> 00:43:02.650
So in the X chromosome, we
see very little contribution

00:43:02.650 --> 00:43:03.790
from Neanderthals.

00:43:03.790 --> 00:43:07.420
It's probably again
to present-day people.

00:43:07.420 --> 00:43:10.810
So it's almost like a
desert, the whole chromosome,

00:43:10.810 --> 00:43:13.670
which is probably also
compatible with that the men

00:43:13.670 --> 00:43:16.280
had particular problems.

00:43:16.280 --> 00:43:22.050
Of course, there are
extra, many genes on the X

00:43:22.050 --> 00:43:24.380
that has to do
with reproduction.

00:43:24.380 --> 00:43:27.105
And males are, of course,
slaves to their X chromosome,

00:43:27.105 --> 00:43:27.960
if you like.

00:43:27.960 --> 00:43:30.230
Men have only one X chromosome.

00:43:30.230 --> 00:43:33.420
So if they get bad alleles,
they are in trouble.

00:43:33.420 --> 00:43:36.820
Whereas females have two
chances also on the X.

00:43:36.820 --> 00:43:39.430
So it's probably again
a reflection of that

00:43:39.430 --> 00:43:42.640
the men may have had a
problem in the hybrids.

00:43:42.640 --> 00:43:45.344
That's the only thing at the
moment we can say about that,

00:43:45.344 --> 00:43:46.630
I think.

00:43:46.630 --> 00:43:50.840
AUDIENCE: The contaminant DNA
